Ahadi Kenya Trust and the World Wide Fund for Nature have donated 6,000 shoes and sandals to the Boni Community in Bar goni, Lamu West, to eradicatejiggers infestations. They also treated residents. Speaking in Bar goni village, Ahadi Kenya CEO Stanley Kamau said jiggers infestation is a hindrance to development.Ahadi Kenya is working with the state and counties to reduce jiggers infestation by more than 50 per cent by next year. Our main objective is to eradicate jiggers completely...The secret is to keep homes clean and use pesticides to kill breeding grounds, Kamau said.WWF Kenya chief executive Mohamed Awer pledged to make health a priority, as it can t preach conservation to sick people .